    <node id="Gravitium">
      <data key="d0">Gravitium</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Gravitium is an element of extraordinary density, predominantly found in the lower lithosphere of certain worlds. It has a unique atomic structure that absorbs and mitigates kinetic force, making it resistant to impact. It also subtly alters local gravitational constant measurements and remains solid even at immense temperatures.&lt;SEP&gt;Gravitium is a substance that exhibits remarkable chemical stability, remains solid at immense temperatures, and can subtly alter local gravitational constant measurements when in extensive concentrations.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fdbdb9446200becfa82435a43d9650c2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6d17ad2ef72f49be20201bc489a66d62</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776379556</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Solara">
      <data key="d0">Solara</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Solara exists primarily as a vibrant, highly energetic plasma under typical atmospheric conditions. Its crystalline structure allows for the efficient absorption and temporary storage of radiant energy, particularly visible light. It emits a weak, distinct energy signature in the low-frequency spectrum and requires specialized containment systems for safe handling.&lt;SEP&gt;Solara is a vibrant, highly energetic plasma with a crystalline structure that allows for the absorption and temporary storage of radiant energy, particularly visible light. It emits a weak, distinct energy signature in the low-frequency spectrum and requires specialized containment systems for safe handling.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fdbdb9446200becfa82435a43d9650c2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6d17ad2ef72f49be20201bc489a66d62</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776379556</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Umbradium">
      <data key="d0">Umbradium</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Umbradium is a new element created by mixing Gravitium and Solara. Its production results in the creation of a localized zone that disrupts kinetic energy transfer and dampens electromagnetic fields.&lt;SEP&gt;Umbradium is a new element created by mixing Gravitium and Solara. Its production creates a localized zone that disrupts kinetic energy transfer and dampens electromagnetic fields.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fdbdb9446200becfa82435a43d9650c2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6d17ad2ef72f49be20201bc489a66d62</data>
